column1: Lab-based schema for identifying each subject
column2: Lab-based schema for identifying each sample, must be unique
column3: sample_id of the sample from which the current sample was derived (e.g., slice, tissue punch, biopsy, etc.)
column4: If data is collected on multiple samples at the same time include the identifier of the pool where the data file will be found.
column5: Experimental group subject is assigned to in research project. If you have experimental groups for samples please add another column.
column6: Physical type of the specimen from which the data were extracted
column7: The organ, or subregion of organ from which the data were extracted
column10: Sex of the subject, or if unknown fill in with “Unknown
column11: Age of the subject  (e.g., hours, days, weeks, years old) or if unknown fill in with “unknow
column12: Qualitative description of age category from derived from UBERON life cycle stage
column13: The minimal age (youngest) of the research subjects. The format for this field: numerical value + space + unit (spelled out)
column14: The maximal age (oldest) of the research subjects. The format for this field: numerical value + space + unit (spelled out)
column15: Preference of the subject to use the right or left hand, if applicable
column17: RRID for the strain For this field
column18: Ignore if RRID is filled in, Genetic makeup of genetically modified alleles in transgenic animals belonging to the same subject group
column20: Once the research protocol is uploaded to Protocols.io, the title of the protocol within Protocols.io must be noted in this field.
column21: The Protocol.io URL for the protocol. Once the protocol is uploaded to Protocols.io, the protocol must be shared with the SPARC group and the Protocol.io URL is noted in this field. Please share with the SPARC group.
column22: A file containing experimental records for each sample.
